Class CCI_I22_MEDICATION_ENCODING_DETAIL

  • java.lang.Object
    • ca.uhn.hl7v2.model.AbstractStructure
      • ca.uhn.hl7v2.model.AbstractGroup
        • ca.uhn.hl7v2.model.v27.group.CCI_I22_MEDICATION_ENCODING_DETAIL
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Group, Structure, Visitable, Serializable

    public class CCI_I22_MEDICATION_ENCODING_DETAIL
extends AbstractGroup

    Represents a CCI_I22_MEDICATION_ENCODING_DETAIL group structure (a Group object). A Group is an ordered collection of message segments that can repeat together or be optionally in/excluded together. This Group contains the following elements:

    • 1: RXE (Pharmacy/Treatment Encoded Order)
    • 2: RXR (Pharmacy/Treatment Route) repeating
    • 3: RXC (Pharmacy/Treatment Component Order) optional repeating
    • 4: OBX (Observation/Result) optional repeating
